1
00:00:05,005 --> 00:00:08,507
In 2026, I, Kosei Neo,

2
00:00:08,508 --> 00:00:10,009
president of NEOXIS,

3
00:00:10,010 --> 00:00:11,810
should have died

4
00:00:11,811 --> 00:00:14,280
<i>when someone pushed me…</i>

5
00:00:16,049 --> 00:00:19,985
I ended up in the body of Eito Nomoto,

6
00:00:19,986 --> 00:00:23,022
who looked just like me
and was supposed to have died

7
00:00:23,023 --> 00:00:24,457
in an accident in 2012.

8
00:00:24,958 --> 00:00:27,626
He was the son of Eiji Nomoto,
the man caught in my fall.

9
00:00:27,627 --> 00:00:28,527
‎EITO NOMOTO

10
00:00:28,528 --> 00:00:30,896
<i>As a condition
of the Vena Bank acquisition,</i>

11
00:00:30,897 --> 00:00:32,865
<i>they're demanding
a large plot of land in Tokyo.</i>

12
00:00:32,866 --> 00:00:37,336
Akari Shopping Street
has no funds left to invest with.

13
00:00:37,337 --> 00:00:39,304
<i>Contact me anytime.</i>

14
00:00:39,305 --> 00:00:40,707
I'll be waiting.

15
00:00:41,408 --> 00:00:42,875
Excuse me.

16
00:00:42,876 --> 00:00:44,277
FEELINGS TOWARD SARASA

17
00:00:47,113 --> 00:00:51,650
The acquisition site will be the Akari
Housing Complex and Akari Shopping Street.

18
00:00:51,651 --> 00:00:54,787
<i>I'll be on the opposing side
from everyone here.</i>

19
00:00:54,788 --> 00:00:57,890
So history truly cannot be changed.

20
00:00:57,891 --> 00:01:01,160
But if this is meant as some kind
of harassment toward you and me,

21
00:01:01,161 --> 00:01:03,529
I will never forgive President Neo.

22
00:01:03,530 --> 00:01:04,230
‎SUSPICIONS ABOUT KOSEI

23
00:01:06,733 --> 00:01:10,035
Could it have been… Tomono?

24
00:01:10,036 --> 00:01:12,005
‎A TORMENTED FUTURE

25
00:01:14,641 --> 00:01:17,977
I have something important
to tell everyone today.

26
00:01:18,578 --> 00:01:21,081
What's up, Tomono?
You're being very formal.

27
00:01:21,648 --> 00:01:25,217
Oh, could it be that
you and Eri are expecting?

28
00:01:25,218 --> 00:01:27,286
- Huh?
- What?

29
00:01:27,287 --> 00:01:28,787
That would be cause to celebrate!

30
00:01:28,788 --> 00:01:32,092
No. I'm here with news
as a member of NEOXIS.

31
00:01:35,061 --> 00:01:36,296
NEOXIS will be initiating

32
00:01:37,464 --> 00:01:41,134
acquisition negotiations
for the Akari Shopping Street.

33
00:01:42,569 --> 00:01:44,838
Buying the shopping street?

34
00:01:45,738 --> 00:01:47,240
What does that mean?

35
00:01:48,141 --> 00:01:52,145
It means we'll pay you
and ask you to vacate.

36
00:01:52,745 --> 00:01:53,746
Vacate?

37
00:01:54,314 --> 00:01:57,382
I intend to work
as closely as possible with you

38
00:01:57,383 --> 00:02:00,252
on the relocation package
and your lives afterward.

39
00:02:00,253 --> 00:02:02,387
Give me a break!

40
00:02:02,388 --> 00:02:03,755
Nobody's leaving!

41
00:02:03,756 --> 00:02:05,125
Get out!

42
00:02:05,625 --> 00:02:08,328
And you call yourself Eri's fiancé?!

43
00:02:09,496 --> 00:02:11,830
I'm disgusted! Get out!

44
00:02:11,831 --> 00:02:13,466
Hey! Get out!

45
00:02:14,300 --> 00:02:15,869
Dammit!

46
00:02:19,339 --> 00:02:20,973
NOMOTO DRY CLEANERS

47
00:02:20,974 --> 00:02:22,008
Tomono…

48
00:02:25,945 --> 00:02:28,814
I'm… sorry.

49
00:02:28,815 --> 00:02:32,785
No. Their anger is
completely understandable.

50
00:02:33,853 --> 00:02:35,221
I think President Neo is offering

51
00:02:35,722 --> 00:02:38,558
genuinely good terms.

52
00:02:39,359 --> 00:02:42,162
But everyone's on edge right now.

53
00:02:43,963 --> 00:02:46,099
But the best I can do right now

54
00:02:46,599 --> 00:02:49,035
is try to secure
the fairest terms possible.

55
00:02:51,171 --> 00:02:53,706
<i>The old me was the same way.</i>

56
00:02:54,941 --> 00:02:57,043
Relocation package… What a joke.

57
00:02:57,544 --> 00:03:00,880
No matter how much they offer,
nobody's going anywhere!

58
00:03:01,481 --> 00:03:04,551
Besides, the shopping street has savings.

59
00:03:05,051 --> 00:03:07,554
About that…

60
00:03:10,456 --> 00:03:14,227
We were trying to grow

61
00:03:14,727 --> 00:03:16,596
those savings for everyone…

62
00:03:17,797 --> 00:03:19,933
We invested in stocks

63
00:03:20,466 --> 00:03:21,834
and lost everything.

64
00:03:22,835 --> 00:03:24,504
- What?
- Huh?

65
00:03:25,305 --> 00:03:26,639
We're so sorry!

66
00:03:27,974 --> 00:03:29,308
How could you?!

67
00:03:29,309 --> 00:03:31,443
Are you serious?!

68
00:03:31,444 --> 00:03:33,445
We haven't had customers since COVID,

69
00:03:33,446 --> 00:03:36,014
and you did that?!

70
00:03:36,015 --> 00:03:39,052
Jeez… What are you doing?

71
00:03:40,653 --> 00:03:42,421
Jeez…

72
00:03:42,422 --> 00:03:43,923
Huh?

73
00:03:44,724 --> 00:03:46,259
Oh, well…

74
00:03:47,894 --> 00:03:48,961
Huh?

75
00:03:48,962 --> 00:03:51,263
Eiji and Kinpei were trying to grow it

76
00:03:51,264 --> 00:03:53,932
for everyone's sake.

77
00:03:53,933 --> 00:03:57,536
And that money only existed
thanks to Eiji's son Eito

78
00:03:57,537 --> 00:04:01,540
and Kinpei's daughter Sarasa
to begin with.

79
00:04:01,541 --> 00:04:05,211
- That's a fair point.
- Yeah.

80
00:04:07,180 --> 00:04:08,581
How about…

81
00:04:10,116 --> 00:04:11,684
we just drink and forget about it?

82
00:04:18,057 --> 00:04:20,960
<i>These people may be
their own worst enemies sometimes,</i>

83
00:04:21,628 --> 00:04:25,298
<i>but that's exactly why I love them.</i>

84
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:29,101
You want Soman's online store
to prominently feature

85
00:04:29,102 --> 00:04:32,938
the shopping street's products?

86
00:04:32,939 --> 00:04:35,173
They're struggling

87
00:04:35,174 --> 00:04:36,942
after a bad investment.

88
00:04:36,943 --> 00:04:38,344
Ichimanda…

89
00:04:39,412 --> 00:04:43,616
You promised to help the shopping street
as a way of making amends.

90
00:04:44,317 --> 00:04:48,787
But the person I most want
to make amends to is Neo.

91
00:04:48,788 --> 00:04:53,259
Supporting a shopping street that's
in opposition to NEOXIS over an eviction…

92
00:04:56,329 --> 00:04:59,097
I believe closing
Super Soman's Arakawa store

93
00:04:59,098 --> 00:05:03,002
is sufficient amends
to the shopping street.

94
00:05:03,936 --> 00:05:05,271
I'll take my leave.

95
00:05:12,945 --> 00:05:16,983
Even with your abilities,

96
00:05:18,284 --> 00:05:20,386
to be in such a bind…

97
00:05:22,522 --> 00:05:24,691
Maybe I can change small things,

98
00:05:25,425 --> 00:05:28,094
but not the shape of the larger future.

99
00:05:29,796 --> 00:05:31,597
Perhaps President Ichimanda

100
00:05:32,365 --> 00:05:35,702
just needs a reason to help.

101
00:05:37,704 --> 00:05:38,538
A reason?

102
00:05:39,839 --> 00:05:41,074
For example,

103
00:05:42,141 --> 00:05:43,943
some future information

104
00:05:45,011 --> 00:05:46,979
that would benefit him…

105
00:05:48,715 --> 00:05:52,952
<i>Using my past-life memories again?</i>

106
00:05:55,121 --> 00:05:59,224
That would really help. I do good work…

107
00:05:59,225 --> 00:06:01,526
Give me more work next time.

108
00:06:01,527 --> 00:06:03,396
Sorry about that. I owe you one.

109
00:06:04,297 --> 00:06:05,765
Well then, okay.

110
00:06:08,034 --> 00:06:10,303
Okay.

111
00:06:11,537 --> 00:06:12,705
Okay.

112
00:06:18,478 --> 00:06:20,178
You're working so hard, Dad.

113
00:06:20,179 --> 00:06:21,413
Yeah.

114
00:06:21,414 --> 00:06:22,682
I'm ashamed of myself.

115
00:06:23,182 --> 00:06:25,251
Trying to get rich easy,

116
00:06:26,285 --> 00:06:28,387
burning through the money

117
00:06:28,388 --> 00:06:29,622
you earned…

118
00:06:30,323 --> 00:06:31,691
I'm a terrible father.

119
00:06:33,259 --> 00:06:37,230
I always loved seeing you work hard.

120
00:06:37,997 --> 00:06:41,033
Losing that money
might have been a good thing.

121
00:06:41,667 --> 00:06:43,369
- Keep at it.
- Yeah.

122
00:06:53,045 --> 00:06:54,212
Here's the proposal

123
00:06:54,213 --> 00:06:57,749
for the relocation package and a
new location for everyone to relocate to.

124
00:06:57,750 --> 00:06:59,651
Ideally, everyone would move
to the same building

125
00:06:59,652 --> 00:07:01,854
and continue working together.

126
00:07:02,355 --> 00:07:05,223
We're paying them to leave.
We don't need to go that far.

127
00:07:05,224 --> 00:07:08,560
And even the relocation package…
Isn't it too generous?

128
00:07:08,561 --> 00:07:10,228
NEOXIS
FOR THE PEOPLE

129
00:07:10,229 --> 00:07:12,064
Let's not be hasty.

130
00:07:13,065 --> 00:07:14,666
"For the People" must extend

131
00:07:14,667 --> 00:07:17,402
to the shopping street residents as well.

132
00:07:17,403 --> 00:07:18,371
Don't you agree, Eri?

133
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:22,407
Thank you for your consideration.

134
00:07:22,408 --> 00:07:24,577
Speed is what matters.

135
00:07:25,311 --> 00:07:27,679
If there are no results by year's end,

136
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:30,383
I'll hand the shopping street
over to Tsuchiya and Takarabe.

137
00:07:33,686 --> 00:07:35,120
NOMOTO DRY CLEANERS

138
00:07:35,121 --> 00:07:36,721
Tsuchiya and Takarabe

139
00:07:36,722 --> 00:07:39,324
would slash the package

140
00:07:39,325 --> 00:07:42,061
and do nothing for everyone afterward.

141
00:07:44,096 --> 00:07:47,033
They might force things through violently.

142
00:07:47,633 --> 00:07:48,701
But Eri…

143
00:07:49,969 --> 00:07:52,905
No matter how much Tomono does for us,

144
00:07:54,006 --> 00:07:56,275
everyone still wants to stay here.

145
00:07:57,677 --> 00:08:01,080
This is our home.

146
00:08:16,028 --> 00:08:19,799
KOSEI NEO

147
00:08:50,963 --> 00:08:52,931
<i>2023.</i>

148
00:08:52,932 --> 00:08:53,865
SPRING STAMP RALLY

149
00:08:53,866 --> 00:08:55,434
<i>Despite everyone's efforts,</i>

150
00:08:56,168 --> 00:08:58,870
<i>the customers never came back.</i>

151
00:08:58,871 --> 00:08:59,938
AKARI-NU

152
00:08:59,939 --> 00:09:03,342
You're removing me
from the shopping street negotiations?

153
00:09:04,043 --> 00:09:06,913
You failed to produce results
by the deadline.

154
00:09:07,980 --> 00:09:11,017
The Akari Housing Complex eviction
is in its final stages.

155
00:09:15,288 --> 00:09:17,856
Is this the president's decision?

156
00:09:17,857 --> 00:09:19,158
Of course.

157
00:09:21,027 --> 00:09:24,630
We'll handle it our way from here.

158
00:09:33,773 --> 00:09:34,740
Thank you.

159
00:09:38,844 --> 00:09:40,346
Thank you.

160
00:09:42,048 --> 00:09:43,182
This is everything.

161
00:09:45,117 --> 00:09:48,987
Tatsu from the record shop
just left the other day too.

162
00:09:48,988 --> 00:09:50,622
Can't be helped.

163
00:09:50,623 --> 00:09:53,626
The days when a bookshop
could make a living are over.

164
00:09:54,126 --> 00:09:58,063
Kinpei, you should shut down
that print shop while you still can.

165
00:09:58,064 --> 00:09:59,831
What are you saying?

166
00:09:59,832 --> 00:10:01,867
I won't let the times beat me.

167
00:10:02,635 --> 00:10:04,103
Chairman…

168
00:10:05,371 --> 00:10:07,940
- No…
- Hey!

169
00:10:09,942 --> 00:10:11,710
Thank you for everything.

170
00:10:11,711 --> 00:10:13,412
Hayashi, take care.

171
00:10:14,447 --> 00:10:16,147
- Call us, okay?
- Okay.

172
00:10:16,148 --> 00:10:16,983
Okay?

173
00:10:17,516 --> 00:10:18,883
Take care.

174
00:10:18,884 --> 00:10:21,219
- See you.
- Take care.

175
00:10:21,220 --> 00:10:22,354
- See you.
- Everyone, take care.

176
00:10:22,355 --> 00:10:23,723
Take care.

177
00:10:24,457 --> 00:10:27,692
If you think it will go your way,
that's a mistake!

178
00:10:27,693 --> 00:10:31,430
<i>Yeah! There's no way we're leaving!</i>

179
00:10:32,164 --> 00:10:34,199
<i>Then how about double the payout?</i>

180
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:36,201
<i>I hope you can see</i>

181
00:10:36,202 --> 00:10:37,669
<i>what a favorable deal this is.</i>

182
00:10:37,670 --> 00:10:39,604
We've been targeting people individually

183
00:10:39,605 --> 00:10:41,440
to break up the group,
and quite a few have left…

184
00:10:42,041 --> 00:10:45,043
But the ones who remain
are quite tenacious.

185
00:10:45,044 --> 00:10:47,612
This approach is a bit…

186
00:10:47,613 --> 00:10:48,481
Tomono.

187
00:10:49,148 --> 00:10:50,249
Watch closely.

188
00:10:51,217 --> 00:10:54,854
People can change completely
depending on the circumstances.

189
00:10:55,554 --> 00:10:56,988
<i>How about five times the amount?</i>

190
00:10:56,989 --> 00:10:58,223
<i>Huh? Five times?</i>

191
00:10:58,224 --> 00:11:01,660
- <i>Huh? Wait…</i>
- <i>Oh…</i>

192
00:11:01,661 --> 00:11:02,994
- <i>Hey, five times…</i>
- <i>Yeah.…</i>

193
00:11:02,995 --> 00:11:06,398
But taking their homes from them…

194
00:11:06,399 --> 00:11:07,466
"For the People."

195
00:11:08,134 --> 00:11:09,268
We're

196
00:11:10,102 --> 00:11:14,005
giving them the money
they'll need to move forward

197
00:11:14,006 --> 00:11:15,141
with their lives.

198
00:11:20,479 --> 00:11:22,814
This isn't what we agreed to!

199
00:11:22,815 --> 00:11:25,917
We pushed through the hard times together.

200
00:11:25,918 --> 00:11:28,920
How can you just cut our orders
out of nowhere?!

201
00:11:28,921 --> 00:11:30,623
Hey!

202
00:11:33,092 --> 00:11:33,926
Dammit!

203
00:11:38,030 --> 00:11:41,266
We’ve cut off almost all
of Akari Shopping Street’s supply lines.

204
00:11:41,267 --> 00:11:44,402
Orders to the factory
have also been stopped.

205
00:11:44,403 --> 00:11:47,472
Their eviction is now
just a matter of time.

206
00:11:47,473 --> 00:11:49,974
Sabotaging their business,
starving them out…

207
00:11:49,975 --> 00:11:53,111
Do you really think that's acceptable?!

208
00:11:53,112 --> 00:11:54,280
Tomono,

209
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:57,717
the eviction
is a direct order from the president.

210
00:12:03,355 --> 00:12:10,329
NOMOTO DRY CLEANERS

211
00:12:15,334 --> 00:12:17,269
Hello, Nomoto Dry Cleaners…

212
00:12:18,104 --> 00:12:18,938
Huh?

213
00:12:20,473 --> 00:12:23,042
President Neo from NEOXIS?

214
00:12:23,609 --> 00:12:25,945
Why not stop being so stubborn?

215
00:12:26,712 --> 00:12:32,451
You and everyone else are all struggling,
aren't you?

216
00:12:34,019 --> 00:12:35,721
<i>Isn't it your duty</i>

217
00:12:36,722 --> 00:12:40,158
<i>as president of the Akari Shopping Street
to ease everyone's burden</i>

218
00:12:40,159 --> 00:12:43,662
<i>and agree to relocate?</i>

219
00:12:44,530 --> 00:12:46,131
I…

220
00:12:46,132 --> 00:12:47,066
<i>100 million yen.</i>

221
00:12:49,235 --> 00:12:53,571
It's your personal reward

222
00:12:53,572 --> 00:12:55,174
for agreeing to the eviction.

223
00:12:55,741 --> 00:12:57,509
<i>Think of it as my gift--</i>

224
00:12:57,510 --> 00:12:58,711
I refuse.

225
00:13:00,279 --> 00:13:02,314
Not everyone is controlled by money.

226
00:13:05,050 --> 00:13:07,620
<i>How does someone like you come to be?</i>

227
00:13:09,121 --> 00:13:10,556
I'd like to meet whoever raised you.

228
00:13:12,458 --> 00:13:13,492
I can only feel sorry

229
00:13:14,727 --> 00:13:16,562
for you.

230
00:13:22,301 --> 00:13:24,403
Well, I didn't see that coming.

231
00:13:25,104 --> 00:13:27,573
Being spoken to like that by you…

232
00:13:28,174 --> 00:13:31,844
Understood. Then let's both

233
00:13:32,778 --> 00:13:36,415
do our best. Goodbye.

234
00:13:46,926 --> 00:13:49,327
- It's okay!
- You're drinking too much!

235
00:13:49,328 --> 00:13:52,030
It's okay! Let me drink a little more!

236
00:13:52,031 --> 00:13:53,598
Hey!

237
00:13:53,599 --> 00:13:54,533
Listen…

238
00:13:55,100 --> 00:13:57,837
What's this about
halting our print orders?

239
00:13:58,404 --> 00:14:01,840
Just the other day,
our flyer printing orders

240
00:14:01,841 --> 00:14:03,642
suddenly dried up too.

241
00:14:04,276 --> 00:14:07,045
Meat and vegetables
aren't coming in at all either.

242
00:14:07,046 --> 00:14:09,514
That's got to be those guys' doing.

243
00:14:09,515 --> 00:14:10,382
Hey!

244
00:14:11,050 --> 00:14:13,718
- The debt is going to keep piling up…
- Hey!

245
00:14:13,719 --> 00:14:15,220
- Are you okay?
- Huh?

246
00:14:15,221 --> 00:14:16,321
I'm okay!

247
00:14:16,322 --> 00:14:17,489
- Oh, no!
- Oh!

248
00:14:18,524 --> 00:14:20,124
Watch out!

249
00:14:20,125 --> 00:14:22,493
- Sorry!
- Hang in there, Kinpei!

250
00:14:22,494 --> 00:14:24,229
What do you mean by "Hang in there"?

251
00:14:24,230 --> 00:14:27,699
Chairman,
how am I supposed to hang in there?

252
00:14:27,700 --> 00:14:30,134
- See you. Thanks.
- Yeah.

253
00:14:30,135 --> 00:14:31,803
NOMOTO DRY CLEANERS

254
00:14:31,804 --> 00:14:32,737
What the heck?

255
00:14:32,738 --> 00:14:34,706
- Thanks. Yeah.
- See you.

256
00:14:34,707 --> 00:14:37,108
- Okay.
- Thanks.

257
00:14:37,109 --> 00:14:38,543
Are you okay?

258
00:14:38,544 --> 00:14:40,179
I'm okay!

259
00:14:40,746 --> 00:14:44,617
<i>At this rate,
Kinpei will follow the same path</i>

260
00:14:45,718 --> 00:14:48,020
<i>as in my past life.</i>

261
00:14:52,591 --> 00:14:54,525
<i>In my past-life memories,</i>

262
00:14:54,526 --> 00:14:56,895
<i>Kinpei passed away</i>

263
00:14:56,896 --> 00:14:58,863
<i>on the day</i>

264
00:14:58,864 --> 00:15:01,900
<i>of Shohei Ohtani's historic
home run and stolen base record.</i>

265
00:15:01,901 --> 00:15:05,270
<i>NEOXIS-TV covered it</i>

266
00:15:05,271 --> 00:15:07,872
<i>on the final day of Silver Week.</i>

267
00:15:07,873 --> 00:15:10,109
<i>September 23rd.</i>

268
00:15:11,744 --> 00:15:12,878
<i>There's no time!</i>

269
00:15:19,919 --> 00:15:20,920
Sarasa.

270
00:15:24,156 --> 00:15:25,257
Where's Kinpei?

271
00:15:26,091 --> 00:15:26,926
Is he okay?

272
00:15:33,732 --> 00:15:36,902
He drinks alone like that every day.

273
00:15:38,437 --> 00:15:41,507
Hey, Eito. You came!

274
00:15:42,041 --> 00:15:44,443
Want to join me?

275
00:15:45,110 --> 00:15:47,546
Come here! Let's drink!

276
00:15:48,514 --> 00:15:50,983
Sit here. Okay.

277
00:15:53,585 --> 00:15:55,053
Okay.

278
00:15:55,054 --> 00:15:57,990
- Is this okay?
- Yeah.

279
00:16:00,426 --> 00:16:02,494
Here. Cheers!

280
00:16:08,901 --> 00:16:10,836
Lately, you know…

281
00:16:12,571 --> 00:16:15,240
I keep thinking about the old days.

282
00:16:18,711 --> 00:16:20,179
Sarasa was three years old.

283
00:16:20,846 --> 00:16:23,549
She was supposed to be in bed,
but we couldn't find her.

284
00:16:24,550 --> 00:16:26,218
Her mother

285
00:16:26,885 --> 00:16:30,823
ran out barefoot

286
00:16:31,490 --> 00:16:33,158
screaming, "Sarasa's gone!"

287
00:16:35,227 --> 00:16:37,261
<i>Everyone in the shopping street</i>

288
00:16:37,262 --> 00:16:39,565
<i>joined the search…</i>

289
00:16:41,133 --> 00:16:42,201
Then…

290
00:16:42,835 --> 00:16:44,970
Beep!

291
00:16:45,471 --> 00:16:47,639
We heard a horn honking.

292
00:16:49,141 --> 00:16:50,609
When we looked up,

293
00:16:51,343 --> 00:16:54,079
Sarasa was toddling down
the middle of the street

294
00:16:55,280 --> 00:16:56,682
with a truck

295
00:16:57,583 --> 00:16:59,784
crawling behind her,

296
00:16:59,785 --> 00:17:01,320
honking away.

297
00:17:03,989 --> 00:17:08,394
Her mother tripped and fell in the rush,

298
00:17:09,194 --> 00:17:10,295
and Sarasa said,

299
00:17:12,264 --> 00:17:16,235
"Mommy, are you okay?"

300
00:17:17,202 --> 00:17:18,637
She was patting her head.

301
00:17:23,709 --> 00:17:24,910
In that moment…

302
00:17:28,213 --> 00:17:29,481
In that moment…

303
00:17:31,150 --> 00:17:32,918
Her mom and Sarasa

304
00:17:33,819 --> 00:17:36,688
were so precious together.

305
00:17:42,561 --> 00:17:44,963
And I was so grateful

306
00:17:45,898 --> 00:17:47,466
to everyone in the shopping street

307
00:17:49,201 --> 00:17:50,502
for looking for her.

308
00:17:53,939 --> 00:17:55,040
And now, because of me,

309
00:17:55,607 --> 00:17:57,910
it's all come to this…

310
00:18:00,712 --> 00:18:02,981
I feel so pathetic!

311
00:18:13,058 --> 00:18:14,526
It'll be all right, Kinpei.

312
00:18:16,428 --> 00:18:18,263
I'll find a way
to save the shopping street.

313
00:18:19,498 --> 00:18:20,899
I'll come back with good news.

314
00:18:25,871 --> 00:18:26,805
Eito,

315
00:18:27,739 --> 00:18:30,776
you're such a kind soul…

316
00:18:33,312 --> 00:18:34,279
You've…

317
00:18:36,748 --> 00:18:38,851
grown into such a dependable man.

318
00:18:50,395 --> 00:18:51,964
- I'm sorry, Eito.
- Yeah.

319
00:18:52,464 --> 00:18:56,033
He seems to be in a really dark place.
Keep a close eye on him.

320
00:18:56,034 --> 00:18:56,869
Yeah.

321
00:18:59,471 --> 00:19:00,739
Are you okay?

322
00:19:02,708 --> 00:19:04,576
<i>I'd heard that Kinpei's suicide</i>

323
00:19:05,577 --> 00:19:08,113
<i>was by hanging.</i>

324
00:19:09,181 --> 00:19:13,452
Sarasa, can I borrow this?

325
00:19:14,019 --> 00:19:16,455
Sure, I guess.

326
00:19:17,756 --> 00:19:18,590
Thanks.

327
00:19:20,893 --> 00:19:22,828
Oh, and that rope too?

328
00:19:33,605 --> 00:19:37,776
You want me to buy
Shijo Corporation's Toyosu land

329
00:19:38,343 --> 00:19:40,913
and transfer it to President Neo?

330
00:19:42,181 --> 00:19:43,615
Did I hear that correctly?

331
00:19:45,050 --> 00:19:49,054
Do you have any idea what that would cost?

332
00:19:52,257 --> 00:19:54,025
I have no reason to go that far

333
00:19:54,026 --> 00:19:57,129
for Akari Shopping Street.

334
00:19:57,629 --> 00:19:58,630
Excuse me.

335
00:19:59,598 --> 00:20:02,768
I want to protect Akari Shopping Street!
Please!

336
00:20:05,037 --> 00:20:06,704
My prediction is that

337
00:20:06,705 --> 00:20:10,341
Meta Goal, a crypto company,
will see its stock surge until year's end.

338
00:20:10,342 --> 00:20:13,878
Buy a lot of it now
and sell it before year's end

339
00:20:13,879 --> 00:20:16,215
for enormous returns.

340
00:20:16,715 --> 00:20:18,684
If you grant my request,

341
00:20:19,251 --> 00:20:22,787
I'll share every prediction I can make.

342
00:20:22,788 --> 00:20:24,156
Ichimanda.

343
00:20:25,090 --> 00:20:26,858
This is extraordinary.

344
00:20:27,859 --> 00:20:29,428
Depending on your decision,

345
00:20:30,529 --> 00:20:32,998
you'd essentially have
a goose that lays golden eggs.

346
00:20:35,367 --> 00:20:36,268
Togo…

347
00:20:37,202 --> 00:20:39,271
it's not the money that moves me.

348
00:20:39,905 --> 00:20:43,208
It's seeing Eito fight so desperately.

349
00:20:44,743 --> 00:20:45,577
So…

350
00:20:46,745 --> 00:20:48,347
I'll do everything in my power.

351
00:20:50,215 --> 00:20:53,218
Thank you very much!

352
00:20:58,690 --> 00:20:59,890
CHANGING HISTORY
COSTS YOU YOUR LIFE

353
00:20:59,891 --> 00:21:03,095
<i>The price is one's life.</i>

354
00:21:03,629 --> 00:21:07,499
You okay? Hey! Eito, are you all right?

355
00:21:12,871 --> 00:21:15,474
The test results came back normal, but…

356
00:21:16,008 --> 00:21:20,911
He keeps drifting back to sleep
the moment he regains consciousness.

357
00:21:20,912 --> 00:21:23,215
It's been happening again and again.

358
00:21:27,286 --> 00:21:28,687
I'll be fine.

359
00:21:29,955 --> 00:21:32,124
Just stay with Kinpei.

360
00:21:33,358 --> 00:21:34,359
At least

361
00:21:35,627 --> 00:21:37,229
until Silver Week is over.

362
00:21:39,898 --> 00:21:40,999
All right.

363
00:21:47,873 --> 00:21:51,076
Dad, you're drinking too much.

364
00:21:56,114 --> 00:22:00,285
You used to say the same thing
when you were little.

365
00:22:00,786 --> 00:22:02,788
- Did I really?
- Yeah.

366
00:22:03,955 --> 00:22:08,026
Always so kind, my pride and joy.

367
00:22:09,161 --> 00:22:12,496
And then going and winning
a prize like that for your art.

368
00:22:12,497 --> 00:22:13,565
<i>You're incredible, Sarasa.</i>

369
00:22:15,567 --> 00:22:19,171
Seeing how happy you were
made me really happy too.

370
00:22:21,373 --> 00:22:22,641
But it sounds like

371
00:22:23,408 --> 00:22:26,244
your ties to NEOXIS are over now.

372
00:22:27,846 --> 00:22:28,847
More or less.

373
00:22:29,348 --> 00:22:31,550
<i>They were an important sponsor for you.</i>

374
00:22:32,050 --> 00:22:34,786
I don't care about that.

375
00:22:35,587 --> 00:22:38,390
I'll just keep painting
what I want to paint.

376
00:22:45,163 --> 00:22:47,733
What do you want for breakfast tomorrow?

377
00:22:48,667 --> 00:22:50,635
Oh…

378
00:22:52,104 --> 00:22:55,005
Maybe Hideko's croquettes and cutlets?

379
00:22:55,006 --> 00:22:56,574
That's all I'd need

380
00:22:56,575 --> 00:22:59,244
to face another day.

381
00:23:01,012 --> 00:23:03,114
- I got it!
- Thanks!

382
00:23:03,115 --> 00:23:05,183
- Time for bed.
- Yeah.

383
00:23:06,017 --> 00:23:07,452
- Good night.
- Yeah.

384
00:23:28,473 --> 00:23:29,708
What time is it?

385
00:23:36,548 --> 00:23:39,151
The final day of Silver Week.

386
00:23:40,318 --> 00:23:41,486
I've got to move!

387
00:23:50,729 --> 00:23:52,129
MUROTA BUTCHER SHOP

388
00:23:52,130 --> 00:23:54,498
Sorry for the wait.

389
00:23:54,499 --> 00:23:56,133
Is Kinpei hungover again?

390
00:23:56,134 --> 00:23:58,002
Yeah…

391
00:23:58,003 --> 00:23:59,570
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

392
00:23:59,571 --> 00:24:00,572
Okay.

393
00:24:04,242 --> 00:24:11,216
IKETANI PRINTING FACTORY

394
00:24:33,038 --> 00:24:34,206
Kinpei!

395
00:24:43,348 --> 00:24:45,417
He's breathing! Call an ambulance!

396
00:24:48,820 --> 00:24:50,956
Sarasa! Call an ambulance!

397
00:25:01,967 --> 00:25:03,502
What did the doctor say?

398
00:25:04,002 --> 00:25:07,506
They can't say anything
until he regains consciousness.

399
00:25:09,040 --> 00:25:11,208
How did it come to this?

400
00:25:11,209 --> 00:25:13,812
It's because of those people
and their eviction.

401
00:25:22,921 --> 00:25:23,755
I'm sorry.

402
00:25:32,397 --> 00:25:33,498
It's my fault.

403
00:25:38,770 --> 00:25:40,739
I don't understand at all.

404
00:25:41,573 --> 00:25:43,441
Explain it so I can.

405
00:25:54,619 --> 00:25:55,487
Togo…

406
00:25:56,721 --> 00:25:57,855
What happened?

407
00:25:57,856 --> 00:26:00,425
<i>It's about the Toyosu land.</i>

408
00:26:01,059 --> 00:26:04,496
President Ichimanda
did everything he could,

409
00:26:06,064 --> 00:26:07,566
but I'm afraid

410
00:26:08,800 --> 00:26:10,569
you'll have to let it go.

411
00:26:12,270 --> 00:26:13,338
I see.

412
00:26:15,974 --> 00:26:17,008
Understood.

413
00:26:25,951 --> 00:26:27,052
Dad.

414
00:26:30,722 --> 00:26:33,425
The president came to visit.

415
00:26:38,797 --> 00:26:40,198
Eito? Huh?

416
00:26:55,680 --> 00:26:57,215
Visit?

417
00:26:59,484 --> 00:27:02,754
- You're the one who drove him to this!
- Stop!

418
00:28:32,477 --> 00:28:33,945
<i>Could it have been Sarasa…?</i>

419
00:28:35,313 --> 00:28:37,282
<i>After what happened to Kinpei…?</i>

420
00:28:40,518 --> 00:28:42,053
<i>Sarasa would never…</i>

421
00:28:47,358 --> 00:28:49,961
Is this what "For the People" means?

422
00:28:52,564 --> 00:28:54,065
Haven't you

423
00:28:54,632 --> 00:28:57,234
lost sight of the ideals you had

424
00:28:57,235 --> 00:28:59,270
when you started this company?

425
00:28:59,771 --> 00:29:03,341
We built social trust
through our welfare business.

426
00:29:03,975 --> 00:29:04,876
We've moved…

427
00:29:06,478 --> 00:29:09,714
into a completely different stage now.

428
00:29:11,916 --> 00:29:13,985
So the welfare work was just a means

429
00:29:14,519 --> 00:29:17,522
to get where you are?

430
00:29:22,761 --> 00:29:23,595
We're in the middle

431
00:29:24,896 --> 00:29:28,066
of a survival game right now,
fighting for the top.

432
00:29:28,800 --> 00:29:30,535
We’ve just got to enjoy it, right?

433
00:29:33,872 --> 00:29:34,973
Tomono…

434
00:29:37,041 --> 00:29:38,409
Why aren't you enjoying it?

435
00:29:40,512 --> 00:29:42,247
I've found the way…

436
00:29:44,516 --> 00:29:46,785
how to rise to the very top!

437
00:29:56,861 --> 00:30:00,031
Just as the people
of the shopping street said…

438
00:30:01,232 --> 00:30:03,401
The one who drove Kinpei

439
00:30:03,935 --> 00:30:06,938
to that point was you. It was us.

440
00:30:19,083 --> 00:30:20,617
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

441
00:30:20,618 --> 00:30:23,721
This is Tomono's letter of resignation.

442
00:30:27,258 --> 00:30:28,626
I see.

443
00:30:33,431 --> 00:30:34,933
Tomono's parents

444
00:30:35,800 --> 00:30:39,003
have been ill,
so things must be rough for him.

445
00:30:40,338 --> 00:30:42,006
As severance pay,

446
00:30:43,541 --> 00:30:46,778
maybe around 100 million yen?
Could you arrange that for him?

447
00:30:48,246 --> 00:30:51,249
I'm sorry. Please ask someone else.

448
00:30:52,450 --> 00:30:55,720
Today is also my last day.

449
00:31:00,592 --> 00:31:01,793
You too?

450
00:31:02,694 --> 00:31:05,129
Thank you for everything.

451
00:31:08,166 --> 00:31:09,133
Eri…

452
00:31:11,536 --> 00:31:12,604
How much do you want?

453
00:31:14,672 --> 00:31:15,940
10 billion yen.

454
00:32:11,496 --> 00:32:12,430
He's been asleep

455
00:32:14,132 --> 00:32:15,300
this whole time.

456
00:32:17,135 --> 00:32:20,571
The doctor says all we can do is wait.

457
00:32:26,077 --> 00:32:29,347
What if he never wakes up?

458
00:32:30,114 --> 00:32:31,182
What should we do?

459
00:32:42,493 --> 00:32:44,929
I want to talk with those of us

460
00:32:45,430 --> 00:32:48,865
who remain about how

461
00:32:48,866 --> 00:32:50,335
to keep the shopping street going.

462
00:32:52,003 --> 00:32:53,371
Before that…

463
00:32:54,272 --> 00:32:56,908
Inose has been offered a chance

464
00:32:57,408 --> 00:33:00,078
to take over
his relatives' factory in Nagano.

465
00:33:00,645 --> 00:33:02,080
Really?

466
00:33:02,647 --> 00:33:06,550
Well, if everyone's staying
in the shopping street,

467
00:33:06,551 --> 00:33:07,552
I'm staying too.

468
00:33:08,219 --> 00:33:09,120
I see.

469
00:33:10,221 --> 00:33:14,092
I don't want to leave
any of you or this town.

470
00:33:15,426 --> 00:33:16,461
Eiji.

471
00:33:17,462 --> 00:33:21,465
Maybe it's time to stop
forcing your feelings on others.

472
00:33:21,466 --> 00:33:22,400
Huh?

473
00:33:23,001 --> 00:33:26,004
Everyone wants to stay.

474
00:33:26,504 --> 00:33:29,874
But if we stay,
we'll all die in the gutter.

475
00:33:31,175 --> 00:33:33,411
Face reality, Eiji.

476
00:33:35,146 --> 00:33:38,483
To survive, sometimes,
you have to let something go.

477
00:33:42,520 --> 00:33:45,757
Inose, Shikanai,

478
00:33:47,058 --> 00:33:48,626
Chono…

479
00:33:49,360 --> 00:33:51,929
They still have a future!

480
00:33:53,564 --> 00:33:57,301
How long will you keep
them tied to this place?

481
00:33:59,670 --> 00:34:03,141
They'll go along with you

482
00:34:03,808 --> 00:34:08,146
because they're good, foolish people.

483
00:34:09,747 --> 00:34:13,317
Can you take responsibility
for their lives?

484
00:34:16,554 --> 00:34:17,822
Our memories

485
00:34:19,223 --> 00:34:21,692
will live on in our hearts.

486
00:34:23,661 --> 00:34:25,629
We can dream of the day

487
00:34:25,630 --> 00:34:28,099
we come together again.

488
00:34:32,203 --> 00:34:35,306
Isn't it time we let go?

489
00:34:41,879 --> 00:34:43,581
I hear you, Hideko.

490
00:34:45,583 --> 00:34:47,618
Just give me a little more time.

491
00:34:48,986 --> 00:34:52,690
I want to try everything I can

492
00:34:53,658 --> 00:34:54,792
before I make that call.

493
00:35:07,105 --> 00:35:08,039
So,

494
00:35:08,873 --> 00:35:11,242
do you have a plan, Dad?

495
00:35:13,911 --> 00:35:14,879
No.

496
00:35:17,448 --> 00:35:18,850
Just grasping at straws.

497
00:35:20,051 --> 00:35:23,187
Maybe something good will come to me.

498
00:35:26,824 --> 00:35:28,826
I've thought about it endlessly.

499
00:35:31,796 --> 00:35:32,997
But it's difficult.

500
00:35:35,199 --> 00:35:36,701
If we'd accepted

501
00:35:37,869 --> 00:35:40,304
Tomono's relocation plan at the start,

502
00:35:41,105 --> 00:35:43,774
everyone could have stayed together.

503
00:36:01,292 --> 00:36:02,326
Dad! This is it!

504
00:36:03,828 --> 00:36:05,329
There's one option left!

505
00:36:07,031 --> 00:36:09,666
SUPER SOMAN'S ARAKAWA STORE
CLOSING SALE

506
00:36:09,667 --> 00:36:11,301
Just as you predicted,

507
00:36:11,302 --> 00:36:13,770
Meta Goal's stock surged to record highs.

508
00:36:13,771 --> 00:36:16,741
We made enormous gains.

509
00:36:19,076 --> 00:36:22,512
And yet I couldn't help
the shopping street…

510
00:36:22,513 --> 00:36:23,848
I'm truly sorry.

511
00:36:25,216 --> 00:36:29,320
So Eito has a request.

512
00:36:30,221 --> 00:36:32,757
Would you consider handing over

513
00:36:33,324 --> 00:36:35,259
the site of Super Soman's
Arakawa store to us?

514
00:36:37,261 --> 00:36:38,262
I see.

515
00:36:38,829 --> 00:36:39,830
If we could move there,

516
00:36:40,331 --> 00:36:43,200
we could start over

517
00:36:43,201 --> 00:36:46,369
right next to our home.

518
00:36:46,370 --> 00:36:49,540
Super Soman's Arakawa store
sits on leased land,

519
00:36:50,041 --> 00:36:54,612
but your relationship with the landowner
is very good, isn't it?

520
00:36:55,179 --> 00:36:57,447
Yes. If we can agree on a price,

521
00:36:57,448 --> 00:37:00,117
there's a good chance we can secure it.

522
00:37:01,385 --> 00:37:03,854
I'm begging you!

523
00:37:04,622 --> 00:37:05,990
Even if it costs me my life,

524
00:37:06,557 --> 00:37:09,694
I want to get this site.

525
00:37:10,928 --> 00:37:12,697
If you feel that strongly,

526
00:37:13,664 --> 00:37:15,499
I'll give it everything I have.

527
00:37:16,567 --> 00:37:17,868
Thank you very much!

528
00:37:19,003 --> 00:37:22,138
‎Dad, Kayo is here too!

529
00:37:22,139 --> 00:37:23,140
Hey, Eito!

530
00:37:23,774 --> 00:37:25,308
There's hope.

531
00:37:25,309 --> 00:37:27,278
Is it the Super Soman site?

532
00:37:28,346 --> 00:37:32,115
Ichimanda promised to do

533
00:37:32,116 --> 00:37:33,750
everything he can to acquire it.

534
00:37:33,751 --> 00:37:36,520
We might be able to start over there,
all of us together.

535
00:37:37,121 --> 00:37:39,223
- That's incredible, Eito!
- Yeah.

536
00:37:39,857 --> 00:37:41,891
Did you hear that, Kinpei?

537
00:37:41,892 --> 00:37:43,560
Good news has arrived!

538
00:37:43,561 --> 00:37:46,497
You need to thank Eito
when you wake up, Dad.

539
00:37:53,971 --> 00:37:56,139
- His hands! They're moving!
- Oh!

540
00:37:56,140 --> 00:37:57,674
- Huh?
- What?

541
00:37:57,675 --> 00:38:00,478
- Kinpei!
- Kinpei!

542
00:38:02,880 --> 00:38:04,014
- He opened his eyes!
- What?

543
00:38:04,015 --> 00:38:05,815
- Kinpei!
- Kinpei!

544
00:38:05,816 --> 00:38:09,086
Can you see us, Kinpei? We're all here!

545
00:38:14,292 --> 00:38:15,259
Am I…

546
00:38:17,662 --> 00:38:19,095
still dreaming?

547
00:38:19,096 --> 00:38:20,431
Dreaming?

548
00:38:21,299 --> 00:38:22,767
I dreamed…

549
00:38:25,002 --> 00:38:26,737
we were all getting excited

550
00:38:27,438 --> 00:38:29,473
about starting over together.

551
00:38:30,641 --> 00:38:34,444
The dream continues right here, Kinpei.

552
00:38:34,445 --> 00:38:36,347
- We'll start over from there.
- Yeah.

553
00:38:36,914 --> 00:38:40,618
Get better,
and we'll have a drink together again.

554
00:38:41,319 --> 00:38:42,820
I'm so happy…

555
00:38:45,189 --> 00:38:47,258
that I'll get to drink
with everyone again.

556
00:38:50,928 --> 00:38:52,063
Thanks!

557
00:38:53,564 --> 00:38:54,632
- Thanks!
- Yeah.

558
00:38:55,132 --> 00:38:58,601
I'm so happy.

559
00:38:58,602 --> 00:38:59,836
Kinpei!

560
00:38:59,837 --> 00:39:01,004
Thanks!

561
00:39:01,005 --> 00:39:03,641
I'm so happy.

562
00:39:04,675 --> 00:39:05,609
<i>At last…</i>

563
00:39:07,278 --> 00:39:08,913
<i>the future has changed.</i>

564
00:39:10,481 --> 00:39:11,381
NOMOTO DRY CLEANERS

565
00:39:11,382 --> 00:39:13,116
We've left NEOXIS.

566
00:39:13,117 --> 00:39:17,121
Together, we plan to start
a welfare services company.

567
00:39:17,955 --> 00:39:21,058
It's what we both
wanted to do from the start.

568
00:39:22,326 --> 00:39:23,894
That's wonderful.

569
00:39:25,062 --> 00:39:27,832
I'm sure Mom would be happy too.

570
00:39:28,866 --> 00:39:31,135
- Do your best.
- Yeah.

571
00:39:34,105 --> 00:39:35,773
What was President Neo like

572
00:39:36,273 --> 00:39:37,842
before you resigned?

573
00:39:39,377 --> 00:39:40,844
No matter what I said,

574
00:39:40,845 --> 00:39:43,647
he wouldn't listen.

575
00:39:44,281 --> 00:39:46,517
Consumed by ambition

576
00:39:47,017 --> 00:39:49,954
and saying he'd found
the path to get to the top.

577
00:39:50,821 --> 00:39:52,556
Maybe President Neo

578
00:39:53,157 --> 00:39:55,693
no longer trusts anyone around him.

579
00:39:57,995 --> 00:39:59,330
But I won't forget

580
00:40:00,131 --> 00:40:03,000
President Neo's principles and vision.

581
00:40:03,901 --> 00:40:06,270
Once the bank acquisition settles down,

582
00:40:06,971 --> 00:40:10,608
I believe he'll return to who he was.

583
00:40:12,710 --> 00:40:14,979
It's better not to expect too much.

584
00:40:16,714 --> 00:40:18,516
The greater the expectation,

585
00:40:19,717 --> 00:40:21,752
the deeper the disappointment
when it's betrayed.

586
00:40:32,029 --> 00:40:33,130
Tomono.

587
00:40:34,832 --> 00:40:37,767
I'm so sorry for everything.

588
00:40:37,768 --> 00:40:41,338
No, you have nothing to apologize for.

589
00:40:43,107 --> 00:40:46,410
Could I have a moment of your time?

590
00:40:47,678 --> 00:40:48,646
Yes.

591
00:40:49,380 --> 00:40:51,549
It's about Eito.

592
00:40:52,082 --> 00:40:53,617
What about him?

593
00:40:55,453 --> 00:40:57,520
I have a feeling he knew
what was going to happen

594
00:40:57,521 --> 00:40:59,690
to my father before it actually happened.

595
00:41:00,691 --> 00:41:01,759
He knew?

596
00:41:02,460 --> 00:41:05,094
He took away the rope and cords

597
00:41:05,095 --> 00:41:08,199
<i>and kept insisting
I stay by my father's side.</i>

598
00:41:08,766 --> 00:41:11,836
<i>He said everything that happened
to my father was his fault.</i>

599
00:41:12,470 --> 00:41:15,338
With the climate products
and the COVID supplies…

600
00:41:15,339 --> 00:41:19,510
He always acted
as if he already knew what was coming.

601
00:41:20,778 --> 00:41:22,379
Actually,

602
00:41:22,880 --> 00:41:26,817
his ability to foresee things
has surprised me many times too.

603
00:41:27,785 --> 00:41:29,920
Ability to foresee things?

604
00:41:30,721 --> 00:41:32,388
He had an accident

605
00:41:32,389 --> 00:41:35,258
where something fell on his head
and he nearly died, didn't he?

606
00:41:35,259 --> 00:41:36,760
Yes…

607
00:41:37,294 --> 00:41:39,296
he was trying to protect me.

608
00:41:40,598 --> 00:41:42,265
Togo believes

609
00:41:42,266 --> 00:41:43,900
that accident may have awakened

610
00:41:43,901 --> 00:41:47,805
that kind of ability in him.

611
00:41:48,305 --> 00:41:49,606
An ability?

612
00:41:49,607 --> 00:41:52,009
The ability to foresee the future.

613
00:41:53,978 --> 00:41:57,581
It might not be an ability.

614
00:41:58,082 --> 00:41:59,783
It might be a memory.

615
00:42:01,585 --> 00:42:05,789
I found this novel in Eito's room.

616
00:42:07,591 --> 00:42:09,593
<i>Memories of the Future</i>?

617
00:42:14,164 --> 00:42:16,534
This page was left open.

618
00:42:17,167 --> 00:42:20,036
"Those who changed history

619
00:42:20,037 --> 00:42:22,907
and achieved success
will have to pay the price."

620
00:42:23,474 --> 00:42:26,477
The price is one's life."

621
00:42:28,245 --> 00:42:31,180
I think that may be why
something about Eito

622
00:42:31,181 --> 00:42:34,118
has always felt off to me.

623
00:42:36,854 --> 00:42:41,158
You mean Eito died once and was reborn?

624
00:42:44,528 --> 00:42:46,163
I'm scared.

625
00:42:46,897 --> 00:42:48,465
But what if…

626
00:42:50,601 --> 00:42:52,001
he's not…

627
00:42:52,002 --> 00:42:55,539
who I think he is…

628
00:43:07,851 --> 00:43:09,620
I have unfortunate news.

629
00:43:10,988 --> 00:43:12,555
Ichimanda was unable to acquire

630
00:43:12,556 --> 00:43:16,026
the Super Soman Arakawa site.

631
00:43:18,228 --> 00:43:19,063
Why not?

632
00:43:19,763 --> 00:43:22,533
Someone moved to acquire it

633
00:43:23,334 --> 00:43:25,469
at far above market value.

634
00:43:31,675 --> 00:43:33,544
Kosei Neo.

635
00:43:45,689 --> 00:43:46,690
<i>Why?</i>

636
00:43:51,595 --> 00:43:52,930
<i>Why does my other self…</i>

637
00:44:03,407 --> 00:44:06,343
<i>torment me this much?</i>

638
00:44:19,123 --> 00:44:19,756
‎NEXT EPISODE
‎FINAL EPISODE

639
00:44:19,757 --> 00:44:22,325
‎At last,
‎the future from that day is coming.

640
00:44:22,326 --> 00:44:25,161
<i>‎Starring the fallen icon, Kosei Neo…</i>

641
00:44:25,162 --> 00:44:28,097
<i>‎Who killed me?</i>

642
00:44:28,098 --> 00:44:31,300
<i>‎Kosei Neo has changed because I met you.</i>

643
00:44:31,301 --> 00:44:33,503
<i>‎Listen to me! The future can be changed!</i>

644
00:44:33,504 --> 00:44:34,137
‎WHAT FUTURE LIES AHEAD?
‎THIS DRAMA IS FICTION

645
00:44:34,138 --> 00:44:35,105
Subtitle translation by: Ken Nishizaki
